# Claude Automation — additions to CLAUDE.md

Append the following section to your existing `CLAUDE.md` so future Claude sessions discover the automation without needing a walkthrough.

---

## Automation (installed)

### Hooks

- `PreToolUse` on Edit/Write: runs `scripts/hooks/pre-edit-safety.sh` (GRS guard, innerHTML warning, index-range reminders) and `scripts/hooks/check-sw-version-pairing.sh` (warns on HTML-without-SW-bump).
- `PostToolUse` on Edit/Write: runs `scripts/hooks/validate-json-edit.sh` when `data/*.json` is touched (JSON validity, Vitest subset).

### Subagents (`.claude/agents/`)

- `clinical-accuracy-reviewer` — **invoke after any edit to `data/notes.json`, `data/questions.json`, `data/drugs.json`, `data/flashcards.json`**. Read-only. Uses PubMed MCP if available to verify citations. Catches Beers/ACB drift, GRS leaks, wrong MCQ correct-indices.
- `schema-guardian` — local mirror of all three GitHub Actions workflows. Invoke via `/validate` before `/ship-it`.
- `content-decomposer` — when attacking the 4,940-line monolith. Produces `docs/DECOMPOSITION_PLAN.md`; never edits `shlav-a-mega.html` directly.

### Skills (`.claude/skills/`)

- `/ship-it` — user-only. Full CI mirror + auto SW bump + commit + push. Replaces the edit-test-bump-commit-wait loop.
- `/weekly-audit` — user-only. On-demand mirror of the cron-driven weekly-audit workflow. Writes `docs/audits/weekly-YYYY-MM-DD.md`.
- `question-schema` — Claude-only background knowledge. Auto-loads when editing `data/questions.json`, `data/notes.json`, `data/drugs.json`.
- `hebrew-medical-glossary` — Claude-only background knowledge. Auto-applies when editing Hebrew medical content.

### Slash commands (`.claude/commands/`)

- `/validate` — dry-run CI mirror via `schema-guardian`.

### MCP servers (`.mcp.json`)

- `supabase` — existing, cloud sync + leaderboard operations.
- `context7` — live docs for Vitest 4, FSRS-4.5, Supabase JS.
- `pubmed` — clinical citation verification. Required by `clinical-accuracy-reviewer`.
- `github` — PR/issue triage. Requires `GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN` in env.

## Claude behavior rules for this repo

1. **Never edit `data/*.json` without running `clinical-accuracy-reviewer` afterward.** Medical content accuracy > code cleanliness.
2. **Never edit `shlav-a-mega.html` without also editing `sw.js`** to bump the cache version. The PreToolUse hook will warn; heed it.
3. **Never commit via bare `git commit`.** Use `/ship-it` so the CI-mirror runs first. If you must, the `scripts/git-hooks/pre-commit` hook is installed as a safety net.
4. **Never introduce a bundler.** The zero-build constraint is load-bearing for the dev workflow.
5. **Never add GRS references.** 2026 syllabus excludes them. Both hooks and CI block this; don't try.
6. **Hebrew medical content** uses the terminology in `.claude/skills/hebrew-medical-glossary/SKILL.md`. When in doubt, ask the user — don't invent translations.
7. **Pushes go to `main` only.** There's no branching workflow here; `/ship-it` enforces this.
